HEADWORD: Hematocrya
<hw>Hem`a*toc"ry*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <grk>a"i^ma</grk>, <grk>a"i`matos</grk>, blood +
<grk>kry`os</grk> cold.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The cold-blooded
vertebrates, that is, all but the mammals and birds; -- the antithesis
to <contr>Hematotherma</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

